SIMPLE: cask
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cask
<hw>Cask</hw> <pr>(k⟦adot⟧sk)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>casco</ets> potsherd, skull, helmet, prob. fr. <ets>cascar</ets> to
break, fr. L. <ets>Quassure</ets> to break. Cf. <er>Casque</er>,
<er>Cass</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Same as <er>Casque</er>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A barrel-shaped vessel made of staves headings, and
hoops, usually fitted together so as to hold liquids. It may be larger
or smaller than a barrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The quantity contained in a cask.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A casket; a small box for jewels.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cask</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cask
<hw>Cask</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To put into a cask.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Casket</ent>⟦br⟧
